article.headline: Wright St 81, Youngstown State 67
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- DaShaun Wood scored a career-high 35 points to lead Wright State to an 81-67 win over Youngstown State on Monday, and the Raiders snapped a four-game losing streak. Wright State (9-10, 5-4 Horizon League) led by as many as 19 points early in the second half. Drew Burleson scored 13 points and Jordan Pleiman added 12 for the Raiders, who shot 50 percent from the floor (29-of-58). Quin Humphrey led Youngstown State (7-13, 4-6) with 15 points. Derrick Harris scored 13 and John Barber added 12 for the Penguins, who have lost two of three games. Youngstown State shot 50 percent (23-of-46).
